editorialSummary.text: Local outfit building custom furniture, including bookcases, entertainment centers & cabinetry.

originalText.text: It's nearly impossible to find someone who does an excellent job when it comes to custom cabinets in Manhattan. Everyone either does the job the way they want and not the way you asked for and on top of that they have hidden fees. Manhattan Cabinetry didn't have any hidden fees and were blunt with me which i liked! I spoke with Connie over the phone and received a quote and within 4 days they were at my house! All I can say is that I love my new cabinets and that they did a hell of a job. Great people to work with and well earned review. Thanks guys!

originalText.text: When we finally found an apartment in NYC we needed a lot of improvements like custom radiator covers, a custom home office for a tight space, and an entertainment center. Manhattan Cabinetry was the one place that could provide it all. They listened to our needs and created the perfect pieces for us. It was also surprisingly affordable compared to what we would have settled for in the stores. We were extremely pleased with the entire experience.

originalText.text: When we remodeled our New York loft we wanted custom bathroom furniture that had an industrial look and feel to it. We asked Manhattan Cabinetry to submit a design. The custom bathroom vanity and wall units they designed were exactly what we were looking for. The finished result was a combination of steel and wood that was truly remarkable. Manhattan Cabinetry exceeded our expectations.
